  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the policy was, with the time, the same business, if it will succeed, it-- it will stop being Jewish and will belong to the-- to the Germans, through the man who was the so-called trustee, or I don't know how to call it in English.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And mostly, it didn't work too long.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It worked a year, a year and a half, or two.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then the Germans took the whole merchandise out of it, and closed, because you have to know that at least 90%, if not more, of these [GERMAN], of these men, whom they trusted, those were the people who got it, because they were-- they were not real Germans.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were all Ukrainians, or half-Germans, or even Poles who spied for Germany before the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as they were-- as an award, as a prize, they got this Jewish property to-- to keep, to manage, to keep, and to steal.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was all together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had a wonderful life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Almost 100% of them didn't come from the town they were-- they were put.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had-- the first one we had was a Ukrainian who was called, so-called, Volksdeutsche.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Volksdeutsche means a half-German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That means a man who declares himself being German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He wasn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He-- he knew German very, very badly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he needed my father to-- to-- to contact him with the Germans, when they came into the-- into the business.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the very beginning, he was-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he was a manager on the-- but only, he kept himself inside, because he know-- he knew his limitations.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All he wanted is to have a very good life, to spend a lot of money, to earn a lot of money, which [INAUDIBLE], because all the money went to him.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
